    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the horizon just looks so much more permanent than the road. like it's the only thing that's actually real. everything else is just... temporary transit. if the itinerary is done, and there's no more road to follow, doesn't it just make sense to just step off the path? to find that stillness in the horizon instead of struggling to keep walking?",
